## Configuration snippets

Set environment lifecycle limits with Go duration strings:

```terraform
resource "ona_organization_policies" "current" {
  maximum_environment_timeout        = "30m"
  maximum_environment_lifetime       = "720h"
  archive_environments_after          = "48h"
  delete_archived_environments_after = "168h"
}
```

Keep the two member project policies together and assign opposite values:

```terraform
resource "ona_organization_policies" "current" {
  members_require_projects = true
  members_create_projects  = false
  disable_from_scratch      = true
}
```

Configure editor and per-user environment limits:

```terraform
resource "ona_organization_policies" "current" {
  allowed_editor_ids                    = ["<editor-id>"]
  default_editor_id                     = "<editor-id>"
  maximum_running_environments_per_user = 3
  maximum_environments_per_user         = 10

  editor_version_restriction = [{
    editor_id        = "<editor-id>"
    allowed_versions = ["<editor-version>"]
  }]
}
```

Configure Ona Agent controls in the `agent_policy` object:

```terraform
resource "ona_organization_policies" "current" {
  agent_policy = {
    mcp_disabled                  = false
    scm_tools_disabled            = true
    scm_tools_allowed_group_id    = "<group-id>"
    command_deny_list             = ["git push --force"]
    conversation_sharing_policy   = "organization"
    max_subagents_per_environment = 5
    allowed_agent_ids             = []
  }
}
```

## Delete behavior

Deleting the Terraform resource reapplies the server-defined policy configuration captured before Terraform first managed the organization. Terraform removes the resource from state only after Ona accepts that reset.

